Problem 4
Calculate the Gradient of the following functions

\(f(x,y)=x+3y^2\),
\(f(x,y)=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}\)


Solution

(a)
\[
\triangledown f(x,y) =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}\\
\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}
\end{bmatrix}
\]
\[
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \frac{\partial (x+3y^2)}{\partial x}
= 1
\]
\[
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \frac{\partial (x+3y^2)}{\partial y}
= 6y
\]
\(\triangledown f(x,y) = \begin{bmatrix} 1\\ 6y \end{bmatrix}\)



(b)
\[
\triangledown f(x,y) =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}\\
\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}
\end{bmatrix}
\]
\[
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \frac{\partial (\sqrt{x^2+y^2})}{\partial x}
= \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
\]
\[
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = \frac{\partial (\sqrt{x^2+y^2})}{\partial y}
= \frac{y}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
\]
\(\triangledown f(x,y) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}\\ \frac{y}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}} \end{bmatrix}\)

